-- Dubai's DIFC plans $700 mln sukuk issue by end-Oct - Governor
-- By Martin Dokoupil
-- Sun Sep 21, 2014 03:36AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 21 (Reuters) - DIFC Investments, the investment arm of the company running Dubai's financial free zone, is seeking to raise as much as $700 million by issuing an Islamic bond, an executive said on Sunday.

The company aims to finalise the deal by the end of October, said Essa Kazim, governor of the Dubai International Financial Centre (DIFC) and chairman of DIFC Authority.